233
00:14:46,020 --> 00:14:49,286
(Mr. Fukaya) Old people can't eat steak anymore. Their teeth are too weak.

234
00:14:49,446 --> 00:14:52,313
I made this to be a replacement for that.

235
00:14:53,759 --> 00:14:55,925
（Muroya）The cured ham also...
（Yoshida）Yeah…

236
00:14:56,097 --> 00:14:58,989
(Mr. Fukaya) This we've been making ourselves for 28 years.

237
00:14:59,014 --> 00:15:01,714
It's a little less salty than the Spanish...

238
00:15:01,979 --> 00:15:04,813
you can feel the sweetness
（Yoshida）I can feel it

239
00:15:05,626 --> 00:15:08,626
(Narrator) 28 years of making cured ham

240
00:15:08,945 --> 00:15:12,412
A carefully crafted product with a hint of sweetness.

241
00:15:13,806 --> 00:15:17,139
Aged slowly for 1 year and 4 months

242
00:15:17,164 --> 00:15:20,098
The umami flavor is brought out to the maximum extent possible!

243
00:15:20,959 --> 00:15:23,826
