250
00:15:44,578 --> 00:15:45,891
A society that forms relations over drinks

251
00:15:45,982 --> 00:15:49,821
Well, in other words, Hakodate's ability to integrate with

252
00:15:49,845 --> 00:15:53,584
the Spanish drinking culture is one of the
most profound things about Hakodate, after all.

253
00:15:56,612 --> 00:15:58,712
Ah~... this.
What are you drinking?

254
00:15:58,737 --> 00:16:00,204
(Woman) Sangria.
(Yoshida) Ah...

255
00:16:00,229 --> 00:16:02,796
It's delicious, too.

256
00:16:03,140 --> 00:16:04,833
I love the Basque Country in Spain.

257
00:16:04,858 --> 00:16:06,958
（Woman）Every year I go two times

258
00:16:06,992 --> 00:16:08,959
(Muroya)
Eh~! Is that so?

259
00:16:09,820 --> 00:16:13,186
(Yoshida) Cheers...

260
00:16:13,213 --> 00:16:15,146
 Oh... a married couple?
(Woman) Yes, we are.

261
00:16:15,171 --> 00:16:16,838
(Muroya)
Did you meet in Japan?

262
00:16:17,058 --> 00:16:18,824
Yes, yes, here.

263
00:16:18,849 --> 00:16:20,816
Here in Hakodate
